'''Green Information Technology''' ('''Green IT''') refer to a systematic application of [[ecological sustainability]] criteria (such as [[pollution prevention]], [[product stewardship]], use of [[clean technologies]]) to the creation, sourcing, use and disposal of the [[Information technology|IT]] technical infrastructure as well as within the IT human and managerial practices that directly or indirectly address environmental sustainability in organizations.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Mithas|first1=Sunil|last2=Khuntia|first2=Jiban|last3=K. Roy|first3=Prasanto|title=Green Information Technology, Energy Efficiency, and Profits: Evidence from an Emerging Economy|journal=ICIS 2010 PROCEEDINGS|url=http://aisel.aisnet.org/icis2010_submissions/11/}}</ref>

